name: #ExtinctHominids - Uncle Homo Habilis
description:
Homo Habilis. Eastern and Southern Africa. Early Pleistocene. Extinct.
 
Nicknamed the ‘Handy Man’, he was one of the first to manufacture stone tools and help usher in the modern butchering industry. He shared the earth with close cousins Homo Rudolfensis, Homo Erectus, and Paranthropus Boisei. 

[Cranium model from El Museu de la Universitat de València d'Història Natural shared under CC BY 4.0]
